===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} {{term|lang=ang|igland|īġland}}.  The S was added by confusion with {{etyl|fro}} {{term|lang=fr|isle}}, which is not related but is instead from {{etyl|la}} {{term|lang=la|insula}}.  Cognate with {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|lang=de|Aue||water-meadow}} and {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|lang=la|aqua}}.  Compare {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|lang=nl|eiland}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|lang=de|Eiland}}, Old Norse ''[[eyland]]'' and {{etyl|en|-}} {{term|lang=en|ey}} as in [[Anglesey]], [[Bardsey]], [[Ely]].

